FT  02 APR 92 / Nigeria triples air fares
Nigeria tripled international air fares and doubled phone tariffs yesterday
after the recent depreciation of the naira to 18.6 from 10.56 to the dollar,
Reuter reports. Airlines said a return Lagos-London economy ticket rose from
8,428 naira (Dollars 453) to 25,200 naira (Dollars 1,355) - equal to two
years' salary for a teacher.
